Section 1:
1 L.D. 1186
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TRANSPORTATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 791, L.D. 1186, “Resolve, Directing the
10 Department of Transportation to Study the Feasibility of Ferry Service to Monhegan
11 Island”
12 Amend the resolve in section 1 by striking out all of the first indented paragraph and
13 subsections 1 to 6 (page 1, lines 6 to 17 in L.D.).
14 Amend the resolve by inserting after section 1 the following:
15 'Sec. 2. Study stakeholders. Resolved: That the Department of Transportation
16 may, but is not required to, invite the participation in the study under section 1 of any of
17 the following as stakeholders:
18 1. A Monhegan Plantation representative, such as the First Assessor or the First
19 Assessor's designee, appointed by the Commissioner of Transportation;
20 2. A year-round resident of the State with a vested interest in Monhegan Island,
21 appointed by the Commissioner of Transportation;
22 3. A representative from a private transit provider that provides waterborne
23 transportation, appointed by the Commissioner of Transportation; and
24 4. No more than 2 representatives from the Department of Transportation, one of whom
25 may be a member who represents the Maine State Ferry Service, appointed by the
26 Commissioner of Transportation.
27 Sec. 3. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
28 appropriations and allocations are made.
29 TRANSPORTATION, DEPARTMENT OF
30 Administration 0339
31 Initiative: Provides one-time funding to study adding ferry service to Monhegan Island.
32 HIGHWAY FUND 2025-26 2026-27
33 All Other $7,000 $0
Page 1 - 132LR1732(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 791, L.D. 1186
1 __________ __________
2 HIGHWAY FUND TOTAL $7,000 $0
31 '
4 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
5 section number to read consecutively.
6 SUMMARY
77 This amendment removes a member from the Senate, a member from the House of
88 Representatives and a representative of the Maine State Ferry Service from the list of
99 stakeholders the Department of Transportation may invite to participate in the study
1100 required by the bill. The amendment adds to the list of stakeholders the department may
1111 invite to participate in the study no more than 2 representatives from the department, one
1122 of whom may be a member who represents the Maine State Ferry Service, rather than a
1133 representative of the department who is not involved with the Maine State Ferry Service.
1144 The amendment specifies that stakeholders that may be invited to participate are appointed
1155 by the Commissioner of Transportation. The amendment also adds an appropriations and
1166 allocations section.
1177 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1188 (See attached)
